abstract: AOL plans to introduce a service Monday to sell ads that will appear next to its search results, which are powered by Google’s Internet search engine.

lead_paragraph: AOL plans to introduce a service Monday to sell ads that will appear next to its search results, which are powered by Google’s Internet search engine.

abstract: On YouTube, copyrighted video clips are far less popular compared with noncopyrighted material than previously thought, according to a new study.
snippet: On YouTube, copyrighted video clips are far less popular compared with noncopyrighted material than previously thought, according to a new study.
lead_paragraph: ON YouTube, copyrighted video clips of movies and TV shows are far less popular compared with noncopyrighted material than previously thought, according to a new study.

abstract: Agence France-Presse, a global news agency based in Paris, said Friday that it had settled its lawsuit against Google Inc., the online search engine.
snippet: Agence France-Presse, a global news agency based in Paris, said Friday that it had settled its lawsuit against Google Inc., the online search engine.
lead_paragraph: Agence France-Presse, a global news agency based in Paris, said yesterday that it had settled its lawsuit against Google Inc., the online search engine, and would allow the Internet company to post news and photos from AFP journalists.

headline.main: News Agency and Google End Dispute Over Use of Material
headline.print_headline: News Agency and Google End Dispute Over Use of Material
